definition.value: A biological substance is a substance which originates from a biological organism.
Any of various biological substances which are organic and produced via natural processes.
Any of various materials created by or originated from animals.
An animal skin treated for human use.

A durable and flexible material created by tanning animal rawhide and skins. The most common raw material is cattle hide. It can be produced at manufacturing scales ranging from artisan to modern industrial scale.
The fetishistic attraction to people wearing clothes made of leather or, in certain cases, to the garments themselves.
A theoretical social phenomenon in which LGBTQIA+ people tend to enter similar social circles and/or groups without necessarily specifying their sexualities and/or gender identities.
The guiding beliefs or ideals that characterize a community, nation, or ideology.
This entry does not cover the use of the word "ethos" in rhetoric.
Any of various guiding beliefs or ideals that characterize a nation.
A cross-dresser who performs in a glamorous manner, especially one who performs at nightclubs and other entertainment venues.
This term may overlap with many kinds of drag.
A person who is gender nonconforming in their refusal to be defined or bound by conventional gender labels and definitions.
A process by which a central system of power dominates the surrounding land and its components.
The policy or ideology of a country seeking to extend or retain its authority over other people or territories, generally with the aim of economic dominance.

The practice or ideology of using economics, globalization, cultural imperialism, and conditional aid to influence a developing country instead of the previous colonial methods of direct military control (imperialism) or indirect political control (hegemony).
Non-binary queer feminist theory.
Pornography which involves any of various forms of animation.

Outside of Japan, hentai is anime and manga pornography. In Japanese, however, "hentai" is not a genre of media but any type of perverse or bizarre sexual desire or act. For example, outside of Japan a work of animation depicting lesbian sex might be described as "yuri hentai", but in Japan it would just be described as "yuri".
Video games involving primarily erotic content.
Any of various Japanese erotic video games.

A worldwide community of fans of anime and manga. Anime includes animated series, films and videos, while manga includes manga, graphic novels, drawings and related artwork. They have their origin in Japanese entertainment, but the style and culture has spread worldwide since its introduction into the Europe and the Americas in the 1990s.
A convention for and/or by persons belonging to a particular fandom.
Any of various conventions involving members of the furry fandom.
A second or secondary identity assumed by a person, which is distinct from a person's "normal" or true personality/identity.
A person's alter ego which is not known to the general populace, most often used in fiction.
A furry character, persona, alter ego, avatar, or identity assumed by a person or player normally associated with the furry fandom.
A language whose phonology, grammar, and vocabulary, instead of having developed naturally, are consciously devised.
A constructed language designed for aesthetic pleasure.
A constructed language designed to be utilized in some fictional context, such as in literature or in film.
A constructed language designed to provide easy, fast, and/or improved communication among all human beings, or a significant portion, without necessarily replacing native/natural languages.
A constructed language used in any of various rituals, typically religious in nature.
A constructed language devised to test a hypothesis or experiment with innovative linguistic features.
A language designed by and/or used by members of a particular fandom.
The clothing worn for very special occasions, such as coronations, graduations, parades, religious rites, and trials.
Clothing which is considered appropriate in the context of formalized occasions, such as weddings or funerals.
A distinctive style of dress of an individual or group that reflects class, gender, profession, ethnicity, nationality, activity or epoch.
Costumes worn by actors in any kind of theatrical production, including films, television, and stage productions.
The term "theatrical" here is broader than its traditional usage.
Costumes worn for particular holidays.

Costumes worn on or around Halloween, a festival which falls on October 31. Halloween costumes are traditionally based on frightening supernatural or folkloric beings. However, by the 1930s costumes based on characters in mass media such as film, literature, and radio were popular.
Clothing worn directly before, during, or after a wedding ceremony.
The dress worn by the bride during a wedding ceremony.
Costumes worn by members of various fandoms.
Animal-based costumes associated with the furry fandom.
Theatrical costumes used to disguise a performer as an animal, monster, or other being. They are used in film, television, or as costumed characters in live events.
A genre of genderswap fiction in which characters swap genders by swapping bodies.
A trope in adaptations of media in which a character, multiple characters, or all characters have their genders "switched" for any of various purposes.
A gender flip specifically involving a real-life historical figure.
One of the "rules of the internet" which speculates that "[f]or every given male character, there is a female version of that character, and vice versa."

A role-playing activity in which a story is told by means of its enactment by an actor or actress who adopts a character—in theatre, television, film, radio, or any other medium that makes use of the mimetic mode.
Cross-gender acting refers typically to an actor portraying a gender "opposite" of their own, or generally to an actor portraying any gender other than their own.
The portrayal of underage characters in sexual situations in slash fiction. The prefix chan most likely comes from the Japanese name suffix used as a term of endearment toward children or women.
